Sentencas: The effective binary diffusivity of H-2 and H2O in a Ni and yittria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode of the solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was measured between 650 and 800 degrees C using an electrochemical cell consisting of an oxygen pump, an oxygen sensor, and a porous SOFC anode pellet.
Titulo: Out-of-cell measurements of H2-H2O effective binary diffusivity in the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The effective binary diffusivity was obtained from the relationship between the current density across the oxygen pump, and the H-2 partial pressure gradient across the anode sample measured using the oxygen sensor.
Titulo: Out-of-cell measurements of H2-H2O effective binary diffusivity in the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The anode limiting current density and concentration polarization were estimated using the experimental results.
Titulo: Out-of-cell measurements of H2-H2O effective binary diffusivity in the porous anode of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)
